<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Ralniv</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-06-26 03:43:36</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>I am trying to do Soulfire quest and need Kindly faction with Preists of Life.  The 2gp donation is NOT the way to go from Apprehensive to Kindly.  I gave much gold and didn't budge the faction.<BR>
<BR>
My advice is to kill the dark elves in camp in Lesser Faydark (near Mistmoore Castle).  I also would try doing the Koalindl fish quest.</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Aindaar</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-07-13 11:10:17</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>There are 2 other ways to do it. Starting out I had indifferent with Knights of Thunder and apprehensive with Priests of Life. Got it to amiable with both (can't seem to get it higher than that and I was able to get the mold for the Ro Greaves with only amiable faction). The Priests of Life wouldn't talk to me so I started at the Paladin guild in S. Qeynos.<BR>
<BR>
You get Good faction with (both quests):<BR>
Knights of Thunder, Priests of Life, Guards of Qeynos<BR>
<BR>
Bad faction with:<BR>
Bloodsabers<BR>
<BR>
Talk to Wolten Grafe, S. Qeynos Paladin guild, he stands in the yard behind the buildings. He has a quest to [crush the undead]. Telling him "i will crush the undead" gets you a chest where you put 6 bone chips and combine to get another chest to return to him (both chests are NO DROP and LORE). I'm not sure if you're supposed to use special chips or just the normal ones but the normal ones do work, and quite well. You get experience, money, and food or water along with your faction increase. I used almost 2 stacks and got to amiable with the Knights of Thunder (Karana faction - for Helm of Ro). Another 2 stacks got me to indifferent with the Priests of Life (Rodcet Nife faction - for Vambraces of Ro).<BR>
<BR>
At this point I did another 2 stacks but stayed indifferent with the Priests. I talked with an NPC cleric (can't remember his name, heading toward the UFO he is the guy on the left before you get to the ramp) and he told me about returning pelts from rabid beasts to Priestess Caulria. I accidentally came across a rabid wolf in Qeynos Hills and killed him. He dropped a diseased pelt that is NO DROP. I took this to the Priestess and got faction, money, experience. I conned her and it was enough, I was now amiable.<BR>
<BR>
My guess is that performing a quest for the people you need faction with nets more faction than getting it from somewhere else. Not sure how true it is, will test my theory in Erud when I go to increase my faction there (from dubious, yuck).<BR>
<BR>
Hope this helps some, good hunting.<BR>
</font></td></tr></table>
